Prefix: There are five different forms of horse racing, listed here with their descriptions:
Suffix: - Formula: The race is over a set number of miles, often a mile and a half or a mile and a quarter. The race proceeds in a serpentine fashion, with the first five horses to pass a given marker being declared the first five finishers. The last three or four laps are often the most exciting as the pace quickens and the competition for positions becomes fierce. - Mile: The race is a mile long. Typically run on an oval course, the race includes a number of turns and straightaways. - Half-mile: The race is half a mile long. Typically run on a rectangular course, the race includes a turn at the end that leads back to the starting gate. - Coyote Ugly: As the name implies, this is a race for dogs, and is sometimes known as the Obedience Trial or Obedient Dog Race. The half-mile course is circular, with the contestants being judged based on how well they obey commands (such as “sit” and “stay”) given by the human trainer. This is probably the most popular of all the races due to its quirky name and unusual setting (usually a dog park or pet store) but it’s still essentially a standard mile or a half-mile race. - Duel: Two horses, or dogs, face off in a race to the end. Sometimes called the “little sister” of the Obedience Trial, the Duel is a simple but thrilling competition to see which animal can outrun or outwit the other. The first animal to reach the end is considered the winner. The concept is the same as in the Obedience Trial, except that it’s usually a straight fight to the death.

When cannabis resins and terpenes are concentrated, the range of flavor available completely blows away that of flowers. The temperature of the nail greatly affects the amount and type of terpenes that you taste, usually with lower temperatures producing better results. A hit at a higher temperature reduces the flavor and increases the irritation to your lungs, so aim for the cooler side of the spectrum. 4. Lungs Full Of Vaporized, Concentrated THC. One thing that’s for sure is that lungs full of smoke are not the same as lungs full of dabs. The way that the vapor expands in your lungs packs a punch that is likely to make you cough. Try not to hold it in for longer than a few seconds or it will only worsen your coughing fit. It’s important to remember that the struggle to breathe will subside, and if you go a little bit smaller next time, your reaction should minimize as well. 5. The Dab Sweats. Anyone that says smoking weed isn’t a workout has obviously never taken a hit from a rig before. Besides coughing like a maniac, the second most common side-effect associated with dabbing is sweating like you ran a mile. The calories burned may not match up, but with a solid indica, you could find yourself in bed within an hour after you exhale. Prefix: Tree percs resemble just that—a tree. Smoke comes up through the “trunk” of that tree (i.e. the main central tube) and down through the “branches” of that tree which have slits at their ends, producing a mess of bubbles and that classic sound we all know and love.. Showerhead percs also look like their namesake—showerheads. A vertical tube flares out at the bottom, with holes or slits along the rim. Smoke bubbles through those openings at the base and into the main chambler before continuing on to the mouthpiece.. Because of their design, showerhead percolator bongs combine well with other types of percolators. They also combine well with additional showerhead percs.. You’re never going to believe this, but honeycomb percs…look like honeycombs (the kind you find in beehives). Are you sensing the trend yet?Honeycomb percolators are flat discs studded with holes, through which the smoke filters. More holes means more bubbles, which is why many feature more than 30 or more. And because of their simple, yet elegant design, they can easily be stacked on top of one another for additional diffusion.. Also known as “circ percs,” the circular percolator is in the shape of…you know what? Nevermind. You already know.. In any case, the diffusion occurs through holes or slits around the rim of a glass circle. Similar in design to the showerhead, circ percs can be found in percolator bongs and even in ash catchers..
Suffix: Thankfully, Matrix percolators do not look like The Matrix. But, like the movie, they will blow your mind.. As far as bong percolator types go, those that feature a Matrix perc are top-tier. Cylindrical in shape, these bad boys offer 360-degree filtration through both horizontal and vertical slits. The complex design makes for extra diffusion and, thus, spectacularly smooth smoke.. Often known as a “swiss percolator,” cheese percs resemble a wheel of — you guessed it — Swiss cheese. Holes pepper the outside of the circular base in an often unpredictable pattern. They offer extra filtration and a cacophony of chaotic bubbles, and make for a unique percolator bong.
